<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A person is dead after being wounded during a mass brawl involving two groups of people at a park in Brisbane's north.</p>

<p>Police have confirmed one death and multiple injuries resulted from the altercation on Sunday afternoon at O'Callaghan Park in Zillmere.</p>

<p>Emergency crews were called to the park on the corner of Jennings St and Zillmere Rd around 5.35pm on Sunday. </p>

<p>Police have confirmed one death and multiple injuries resulted from the altercation on Sunday afternoon at O'Callaghan Park in Zillmere</p>

<p>It is understood the fight involved stabbing weapons and a number of young Sudanese men in their early 20s, the Courier Mail reports. </p>

<p>It's believed one of the groups was sitting in the park when the other group arrived and the altercation was sparked.</p>

<p>Some of the people involved are believed to have fled the scene when police arrived.</p>

<p>A Queensland Ambulance spokeswoman confirmed multiple patients had been transported to hospital and a crime scene had been established.</p>

<p>More to come.  </p>
